OL,6,FDr Frances O'Hagan, chair of the BMA
OL,7,FNorthern Ireland General Practitioners
OL,8,FCommittee said: "We cannot overstate
OL,9,Fthe severe financial pressures Family
OL,10,FPractitioner Services in Northern
OL,11,FIreland collectively are now under.
OL,13,F"This will inevitably mean increased
OL,14,Fpatient access issues, further
OL,15,Fshrinkage of Health Service dentistry
OL,16,Fin NI, further closure of general
OL,17,Fpractices and community pharmacies,
OL,18,Fand reduced access to NHS services in
OL,19,Foptometry practices caused by the
OL,20,Fremoval of automatic access to care
OL,21,Ffor those patients on universal credit.
